.TH "calipso_map_cat_hton" 9 "calipso_map_cat_hton" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
calipso_map_cat_hton \- Perform a category mapping from host to network
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" calipso_map_cat_hton
.BI "(const struct calipso_doi *doi_def "  ","
.BI "const struct netlbl_lsm_secattr *secattr "  ","
.BI "unsigned char *net_cat "  ","
.BI "u32 net_cat_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "doi_def" 12
the DOI definition
.IP "secattr" 12
the security attributes
.IP "net_cat" 12
the zero'd out category bitmap in network/CALIPSO format
.IP "net_cat_len" 12
the length of the CALIPSO bitmap in bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Perform a label mapping to translate a local MLS category bitmap to the
correct CALIPSO bitmap using the given DOI definition.  Returns the minimum
size in bytes of the network bitmap on success, negative values otherwise.
